I see the same code in 2 classes above (except MultiTenantNamespaceProjectDriver). Perhaps it could be extracted as a function which returns project_id. Like:

    NEUTRON_PID = config.CONF.neutron_defaults.project

    def get_project(obj):
        np = obj['metadata']['namespace']
        net_crd = driver_utils.get_kuryrnetwork_crd(np)
        project_id = net_crd['spec'].get('projectId', NEUTRON_PID)

        if not project_id:
            raise cfg.RequiredOptError('project', cfg.OptGroup('neutron_defaults'))

        return project_id

and than use it like:

    class MultiTenantNetworkPolicyProjectDriver(base.NetworkPolicyProjectDriver):

